column620: some trends I followed: I recognized towards the end that I like the study of history than to hear that a new genocide or new funeral or new unit of an event relates to death occured so for this reason towards the end of the survey, i tried to choose terms that were plural for events related to death or crime: genocides, assasinations, prisons. This is all because I'd prefer to study the past history of such negative events than to hear that a new single negative event has occured. Studying the past vs. hearing that a new single event has occured in the future would make me more happy. However, at the beginning of the survey to respond to what made me more happy I just selected plural of things that were good in my own view such as money and single of things that are not as comfortable or more negative. For the response of what seems small I tried to choose singular items. For the response of what seems big I tried to choose plural items.
